 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-3d1","title":"Epic: First-Run Setup Wizard with Validation","description":"## Overview

Implement an interactive setup wizard that takes a user from "installed" to "working" with minimal friction. The wizard should validate the local environment, provision or validate workers, install hooks for detected agents, and run an end-to-end verification build.

This bead must integrate documented agent config locations (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI) and offer optional auto-install of missing local dependencies (rsync, zstd, rustup) with explicit user consent.

## Goals

1. One-command setup path: `rch setup`
2. Validate local prerequisites (rsync, zstd, ssh, rustup)
3. Guide worker configuration with SSH validation
4. Detect agents and install hooks where supported
5. Run a real end-to-end verification build
6. Safe to re-run (idempotent)

## CLI Interface

```
rch setup                     # Full interactive wizard
rch setup --quick             # Minimal prompts
rch setup --check             # Validate only
rch setup --worker <host>     # Non-interactive single worker add
rch setup --install-deps      # Auto-install missing local deps (with confirmation)
```

## Wizard Flow (Updated)

1. Local Prerequisites
   - Check: rsync, zstd, ssh, rustup
   - If missing and `--install-deps` set, offer auto-install via OS package manager
   - Otherwise provide exact install commands and continue in "warn" state

2. Worker Configuration
   - Collect host, user, key path
   - Test SSH connectivity
   - Detect worker capabilities (cores, disk, rsync, zstd)
   - Offer to auto-install missing worker deps (optional)

3. Config Files
   - Create or update `~/.config/rch/config.toml`
   - Create or update `~/.config/rch/workers.toml`

4. Daemon
   - Start daemon (foreground/background)
   - Verify socket exists and responds

5. Agent Hooks
   - Detect installed agents:
     - Claude Code (settings.json, PreToolUse)
     - Gemini CLI (settings.json, pre_tool_use)
     - Codex CLI (config.toml; detect only if hook schema unknown)
   - Install hooks where supported and safe
   - Summarize hook status for each agent

6. Verification
   - Run an end-to-end build using a temp Rust project
   - Confirm artifacts returned locally

## Auto-Install Strategy

- Local OS detection (Linux/macOS)
- Use explicit package manager commands:
  - macOS: `brew install rsync zstd`
  - Debian/Ubuntu: `apt-get install rsync zstd`
  - Fedora/RHEL: `dnf install rsync zstd`
  - Arch: `pacman -S rsync zstd`
- Require confirmation before running package installs

## Output Requirements

- Human-readable steps with progress indicators
- JSON output in `--check` mode for agent automation
- Idempotent behavior (never overwrites without explicit confirmation)

## Tests

- Unit: detection of prerequisites and OS package manager
- Unit: agent detection + safe hook writes
- Integration: wizard in mock mode with fake workers
- E2E: verify the end-to-end test build

## Acceptance Criteria

- Wizard completes with 0 failures on a fully configured system
- Missing local deps are detected and install guidance is shown
- Agent hooks installed for Claude Code and Gemini CLI when present
- Codex CLI is detected and reported safely
- End-to-end verification build succeeds in mock mode

